---
title: Skillet Refried Black Beans with Southwest-Spiced Rice, Pico de Gallo, Radishes & Creamy Guac
description: We have a serious weakness for the creamy texture and richly-spiced flavor of refried beans. Here, they star in a hearty skillet layered with a bounty of sauces and toppings. Black beans are simmered with onion and Southwest spices, then mashed until smooth and sprinkled with a Mexican cheese blend. It’s all broiled until melty, served with spiced rice, and piled with creamy guacamole, crisp pickled radish and onion, refreshing pico de gallo, and cilantro. Be sure to snap a photo of all that deliciousness before digging in!
